      <description>&lt;h2 id=&#34;ovpn&#34;&gt;Ovpn&lt;a class=&#34;anchor&#34; href=&#34;#ovpn&#34;&gt;#&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/h2&gt;&#xA;&lt;div class=&#34;highlight&#34;&gt;&lt;pre tabindex=&#34;0&#34; style=&#34;color:#f8f8f2;background-color:#272822;-moz-tab-size:4;-o-tab-size:4;tab-size:4;-webkit-text-size-adjust:none;&#34;&gt;&lt;code class=&#34;language-bash&#34; data-lang=&#34;bash&#34;&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;display:flex;&#34;&gt;&lt;span&gt;sudo openvpn --config ~/lab_Trungle256.ovpn &amp;gt; /dev/null 2&amp;gt;&amp;amp;&lt;span style=&#34;color:#ae81ff&#34;&gt;1&lt;/span&gt; &amp;amp;&#xA;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;display:flex;&#34;&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;color:#75715e&#34;&gt;## Detach ovpn process out of current terminal&lt;/span&gt;&#xA;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;display:flex;&#34;&gt;&lt;span&gt;disown&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;h2 id=&#34;interactive-shell&#34;&gt;Interactive shell&lt;a class=&#34;anchor&#34; href=&#34;#interactive-shell&#34;&gt;#&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/h2&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;Before we even get a shell, first switch to &lt;code&gt;bash&lt;/code&gt; shell on our attacker machine first, since &lt;code&gt;zsh&lt;/code&gt; is not going to work correctly&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;div class=&#34;highlight&#34;&gt;&lt;pre tabindex=&#34;0&#34; style=&#34;color:#f8f8f2;background-color:#272822;-moz-tab-size:4;-o-tab-size:4;tab-size:4;-webkit-text-size-adjust:none;&#34;&gt;&lt;code class=&#34;language-sh&#34; data-lang=&#34;sh&#34;&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;display:flex;&#34;&gt;&lt;span&gt;kali$&amp;gt; bash&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;p&gt;Then, after establishing a revshell with target, &lt;strong&gt;on the reverse shell&lt;/strong&gt;, we spawn a interactive shell&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;div class=&#34;highlight&#34;&gt;&lt;pre tabindex=&#34;0&#34; style=&#34;color:#f8f8f2;background-color:#272822;-moz-tab-size:4;-o-tab-size:4;tab-size:4;-webkit-text-size-adjust:none;&#34;&gt;&lt;code class=&#34;language-sh&#34; data-lang=&#34;sh&#34;&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;display:flex;&#34;&gt;&lt;span&gt;target$&amp;gt; python3 -c &lt;span style=&#34;color:#e6db74&#34;&gt;&amp;#39;import pty; pty.spawn(&amp;#34;/bin/bash&amp;#34;)&amp;#39;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;p&gt;We need to pause our current shell listener (maybe &lt;code&gt;netcat&lt;/code&gt;) to connect our pty to the reverse shell&lt;/p&gt;</description>
    </item>
